name: FIT Japanese Store
directions: Second floor,  on your right when coming from the side street. Store entrance accessible from the 2nd floor of garage.
comment: Just act as if you're browsing. The bathrooms are in the back. Hard to miss.

name: Lowe's Rochester, MN
directions: Next to the restrooms for "women" and "men". Tan door on the left side of the hallway, just to the right of the mens room.

name: DSW
directions: Gendered single stall with handicap bars and changing table in the women's room

name: South Street Burger Co.
directions: Right hand side of the store.
comment: Don't need to buy anything to use them.

name: Top Pot Donuts/Rudy's Barbershop
directions: Restrooms inside, between the two shops, accessed by hallway
comment: Bathrooms large enough for disabled customers/have handle bars to help with standing but difficult to access through narrow hallway

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Straight back from entrance doors, in hallway next to sample counter
comment: Try the samples while you're there- usually they're really good!

name: UNBC
directions: Inside the library building to the right of the circular Agora courtyard. The bathroom is on the first floor
comment: Only available during the library's open hours

name: south eugene high school
comment: you have to be a student

name: Howard County Library Savage Branch
directions: Located all the way in the back by the employee offices. Other restrooms in the building are gendered and not single stall. Ask where the study rooms are and the restroom is on the opposite side of the hallway.

name: Mom's Organic Market
directions: Located in stockroom- employees will guide you.
comment: There are two unisex single stall bathrooms at this location. Company is also trans-friendly and has trans employees at multiple locations.

name: ImprovBoston
directions: Ask at desk, if needed for a safe space, it will be available without paying.
comment: Theatre is usually open between hours of 6pm - 12am (Wed. - Sun.)

name: North Dakota Heritage Center
directions: To the right of the information booth near the cafe
comment: Museum is free to enter. Probably polite to at least browse.

name: The Pinhook
directions: Down past the bar and immediately to the left by the arcade machines
comment: It is a bar, and is therefore only open in the evenings. Parking is limited in the area.

name: Myer Farm Distillers
directions: Straight through the door
comment: MFD is a safe place with courteous staff and some excellent spirits and cocktails to boot

name: KEYS CAFE
directions: In the lobby, towards the back end
comment: "officially" for customers but nobody will say anything

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: By the ordering station.

name: UNO Arts & Sciences Hall
directions: 4th floor
comment: The water pressure and sound of water going through the pipes is quite loud in this bathroom so don't be alarmed or try a different bathroom if you have a sensory problem

name: Apple Store
directions: Past the door on the right in the back of the store, on the left wall.
comment: If you ask any employee they'll direct you.

name: The Harley School
directions: Over by the greenhouse on the main floor, a rest room for people of all gender identities

name: Joella's Hot Chicken
directions: Towards the back. There's a huge sign.
comment: It's a small place but it's always pretty busy there so you probably won't be noticed.

name: Mischler's Florist
directions: Way in the back in a little hallway. Ask for directions, they'll tell you the way.
comment: There are 3 small bathrooms in the hallway. Two are labeled (gendered, but single-stall). An unlabeled third one is up a few stairs at the end.

name: Nacoochee Village Tavern & Pizzeria
directions: Back or the resteraunt near the bar

name: Antidote Coffee
directions: Enter the left-most glass door, then head straight back the only hallway. Both restrooms are gender neutral and the one on the left is wheelchair accessible.
comment: Prefer paying customers, but most baristas will let you use the restroom anyway.

name: Grand Prairie Memorial Library
directions: Just inside the front door to the left are two single-stall  unisex restrooms.One other single stall restroom in the Children's area.

name: Tillicum Mall
directions: There is a single stall accessible bathroom in the downstairs public washrooms

name: Fuze Buffet & Bar
directions: right next to the other bathrooms. family bathroom, single stall.

name: Community College of Rhode Island (Knight Campus)
directions: Third floor - at very end of the foreign languages department hallway that is parallel to the 2nd floor ramp - by rooms in the 3100s

name: Freehold Raceway Mall
directions: In the food court
comment: It's a "family" bathroom

name: Barnes & Noble
comment: Barnes & Noble has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: Lotus Kitchen
directions: Past the shuttered closet and it had an octopus painted on the door.

name: Starbucks
directions: On a college campus
comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: Los Aguachiles
street: Río Missouri, Zona Valle de Santa Engracia, 66268
directions: Bathrooms.
comment: Just if you're eating there.

name: Surf City Billiards Bar and Cafe
directions: Hallway to the left at the top of the stairs, near ping pong table.
comment: Security guards often check IDs at the door on weekend nights; must be 21+ when they're out there.

name: Westgate High School
directions: Two all-gender washrooms with single stall in music wing
comment: For students. I think it's pretty accessible, large stall, ramps in music wing. Accessibility not specified though.

name: Artisans Gallery
directions: Unmarked door in the hallway
comment: Pretend to browse for a bit

name: Harrisville General Store
directions: In the back of the store
comment: don't have to be a paying customer to use, staff are friendly and helpful. Single use room.

name: Elkhart Public Library
directions: Second floor in the back corner of the Newspapers and Magazines area.
comment: Public Library, open to all.

name: Halifax Central Library
directions: There's a single accessible "family" stall on each of the first three floors.
comment: Don't worry about looking like you're browsing, no one minds.

name: Coffee Bean and Tea Leaf
comment: Gender neutral and single stalled. Don't need to be a paying customer.

name: College of Creative Arts
directions: On the first floor from the front entrance. After heading inside, it's only a short walk to the left.

name: Professional Center
directions: Near the back of the 1st floor off a short hallway outside the Lawtons entrance.

name: Corridor
directions: Ground floor past the bar towards the kitchen. There is a big sign pointing to it!!!

name: Farmer House Museum
directions: Ask the staff, they are very friendly and both queer community members. Two single use non-gendered bathrooms, one in the caretakers apartment and the other in the collection storage area.

name: York River Crossing Cinema
directions: Right near the other bathrooms. You'll see it before you see the other bathrooms.

name: Monroe County Public Library
directions: In Children's section on the ground floor. Two large handicapped accessible non-gendered bathrooms.

name: First floor, Downtown Transit Center, Lee P. Brown Administration Building (METRO headquarters)
directions: Go into the front entrance, past the front help desk and towards the hall that contains the help desks. The bathrooms are on the right-hand-side of the hall, next to some water fountains.
comment: Gendered single-occupancy restrooms.

name: The Coop (Massachusetts Ave)
directions: Third floor towards the back of the building.  Turn right at the top of the stairs or take a right coming out of the elevator and head towards the study guides.
comment: There are also two unisex single-stall restrooms across the bridge in the Palmer/Brattle St building.

name: The Coop (Palmer/Brattle Street)
directions: Two single-stall gender neutral bathrooms on the 3rd floor of the Palmer/Brattle St building.  They can also be reached by crossing a bridge from the 3rd floor of the Massachusetts Ave building.
comment: I marked these as "not accessible" because one restroom has two sets of doors which might be difficult for anyone using a wheelchair or other mobility aid.  If someone has a better sense of their accessibility please submit a correction!

name: Sunrise Mall Food Court
directions: Near the food court entrance

name: Zoobie's Old Town Tavern
comment: Two single stall restrooms (I believe accessible) previously binary-labeled, now unisex. Go by signs, not the binary murals.

name: Lorain Historical Society
directions: Second floor opposite of the children's exhibit; bathrooms downstairs are also safe space but are gender separated
comment: Tours are 10AM-3PM on Tuesdays and Thursdays and cost $3, but you can also just go to the gift shop and buy a $0.50 card or something

name: Olin Health Center
comment: I believe all restrooms in Olin are "All-Gender." Definitely the first floor east hall by the cafeteria. Accessibility unknown.

name: Muenster University Center, University of South Dakota
directions: Entering the MUC from the guest parking lot on the west side of the building, head straight and make a right down the main walkway there (at the UBrew). The restroom is on the left of the walkway, just before the link that connects to the I.D. Weeks Library, next to a residential dining dishes drop-off.
comment: You don't have to be affiliated with the university to use the facility. Parking in the guest parking lot is metered.

name: Potbelly Sandwich Shop
directions: At the side door entrance
comment: Supposed to be a paying customer but if you ask when it's not busy they usually let you. Need a key.

name: Central Connecticut State University
directions: First floor of the Social Sciences building. Go past the sitting area of you are entering from the side closer to Welte Garage. The bathrooms will be on your right.
comment: you don't even need to be a student to get in

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back by the produce section

name: Christopher Newport University
directions: All main buildings (library, DSU, Luter, Forbes, and McMurran) have single toilet bathrooms.

name: The Stand Juice Company
directions: From the front entrance, walk past the pre-made sandwiches and look to your left.
comment: Unisex single stall restroom - Did not have to make a purchase to use. The food is far too expensive and inconsistent, but definitely safe and inviting.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: All the way to the right, near the stairs, "family bathroom."
comment: Take a lap around the store maybe, if you don't wanna seem like you're just there for the toilet, not often a wait but there's a seating area right near the bathroom you can chill in.

name: Target
directions: Take a right when you walk in, also have family restrooms

name: Time Out Youth
directions: Come in through front door, go into main hallway, door all the way on the left
comment: As TOY is a youth safe space, you have to sign in to enter, and usually only those under 18 can stay. Bathroom contains free condoms, toiletries, and a mirror + sink. Staff is extremely accommodating and are all queer in some way themselves. If you are a homeless queer youth, I know it's a safe place to stay up until about 8:00 at night out of the heat, with friendly youth and staff. Staff can provide you with many programs to help with finding housing.

name: Chocopologie
directions: In the back, to your right.
comment: Very friendly staff and good food/coffee - On occasions when I just needed to use the restroom and didn't make a purchase, I had no problem doing so.

name: Tazza Cafe Inc.
directions: In the back, to your right.
comment: Single Stall Unisex (toilet, no urinal)

name: Old Capitol Books
directions: At the back-left of the store, just ask at the front desk for a key to use it.
comment: You do not need to be a customer to use the bathroom, you just have to ask for the key at the front desk.

name: Taco Hut
directions: Right when you walk in to the restaurant (unless you go through the exit) and to the right, there is both a male and female bathroom door. Although it isn't unisex, it is a single bathroom and able to be locked!
comment: You could honestly just walk right in to the restaurant and use the bathroom, no one notices or minds. Though beware, there are a lot of students who come in to Taco Hut after school hours since it is right next to a high school. And some days during the marching season the restaurant is flooded with band kids.

name: Columbia County Library
directions: The lobby has gendered, multi-stall bathrooms, but the library itself has 3 gender neutral, single restrooms. One is in the upstairs (entrance level) area of the library near the elevator. Another is at the back of the children's library (family restroom with changing table). The other is on the downstairs/bottom level of the library behind the stairs and past the CD racks.
comment: People come in asking where the restrooms are all the time. You don't have to check out a book or be a library patron to use the restrooms.

name: Cher's Ice Cream Shop
directions: On the far side of the shop. Just enter through the front door and walk straight past the booths.
comment: Dave, the man working at the counter, might talk to you. He's just being friendly!

name: Sonic
directions: It's on the outside of the building on the side that faces the pet store.
comment: You don't have to be a costumer or anything, and pretty much the only people who use it are the employees. The busiest times are between noon and 4:00PM and the majority of the customers are elderly so I'd be careful around that time.

name: Coldspring Area Public Library
directions: Just to the left of the entrance.
comment: You have to be a patron and have to ask the front desk for a key, as the bathroom is locked. It's a locking, single-occupancy, unisex bathroom with a urinal, toilet, and a sink.

name: Menchie's
street: Unit 3, 8808 96a St, Fort St John, BC V1J 6E2
directions: Straight at the back of the store

name: Cafe Brio
directions: Back of the restaurant marked "Either or"
comment: Should be a paying customer...

name: Boston Tea Party
directions: Upstairs

name: Huddle House
directions: To the left after entering

name: Sonic Drive In
directions: Back of Building there's a door, go through it & it's on the right

name: The Yolk Cafe
comment: Just say hello and let them know you need the restroom!

name: Del Norte County Library
directions: In the door and directly to the left.

name: DeWitt Wallace Library  (Macalester College)
directions: Second floor and fourth floor (southeast corner of building)

name: Louis St Laurent junior and senior high school
directions: Upstairs in the Louie wing, northernmost door in the west hallway. When you open that door, there's a short hall and to the left a door. That door is the bathroom.
comment: Closed in July, August, and weekends but if you look like a teenager you can just walk in.

name: Solano Community College
directions: Building 1600 on the Solano CC map. It's next to the roundabout and the gym along with the math building.
comment: Not a ton of people use it but it's a private stall that's pretty much clean and nice 97% of the time. The surrounding classrooms are for salon training, child development, peace and nonviolence, and the demographic in that building tends to be mostly female. No one will care if you go inside tbh. Be careful of wasps and mosquitoes on campus. (I can't remember if it's accessible.)

name: Mercer County District Library
directions: Through the front door, walk straight a bit, all the way down the hallway, marked as handicap bathroom
comment: Simply ask staff where the bathrooms are if need be. Don't need to purchase anything.

name: Pet Pantry Warehouse
directions: Straight ahead, first door on left
comment: You don't have to buy anything.

name: South Tahoe High school
directions: Across from the library in the office.
comment: you're allowed to be there even though it says staff only

name: Target
directions: by pharmacy

name: Starbucks
comment: probably have to buy something

name: Matts Cavalcade of Comics
directions: All the way in the back of the browsing area
comment: Act like you are there to buy something, browse for a little, maybe even buy a small thing (there are items less than a dollar to buy, maybe one of those)

name: Starbucks
directions: Just inside the entrance, to the left.

name: University of the Pacific DeRosa University Center
directions: Bottom floor, to the right of the staircase in front of the main entrance. There are gendered bathrooms below the stairs, but a bit further is a hall with a unisex bathroom. Staff are kind and can guide you there.

name: Loyalist collegiate and vocational institute
directions: Walk into the attendance office then turn right.
comment: For any staff or students
